    "#Q3. How does the choice of base learner affect the bias-variance tradeoff in bagging?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0003d2dc-e358-45f2-98e5-886b425bb166",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In general, using a base learner with high variance and low bias can lead to a reduction in variance and an increase in bias. \n",
    "\n",
    "This is because bagging reduces variance by averaging over multiple models, so using a base learner with high variance can lead to a greater reduction in variance"
   ]
